latestPosts.caption:
Hi everyone. Got a few newbies so here’s a little bit about me😊⬇️ 

My name is Thaya (pronounced tay-uh), the owner of Beon Esthetics. I’m 24. 

I started my business under a different name when I was a sophomore in college as a side hustle and have been lashing ever since. I have two degrees, a BS in Public Health and my MPH. I’ve always had a passion for health, but the more I dove into lashing, the more I grew a passion for it too. I fell in love with the freedom of working for myself and now I don’t use either degrees 🌝. Shortly after graduating with my masters, I went straight into esthetician school to get my esthetician license.

My parents are from Haiti🇭🇹 . I’m fluent in Haitian Creole and can speak un poquito Espanõl. I am a child of God, a travel connoisseur, a gym freak, and a foodie😝. I’m definitely more of an experience type of girl vs material.

Ngl I’m a very humble person so I hate talking about myself so this was kind hard  lol but… I do want to say that I love helping other lash artists thrive into their most elevated and most capable selves especially with areas that I once struggled in (ifykyk😅). I hope to be the example that anything you want to do is possible if you put God first and put in the work🤍. Thank you for being a part of my journey ✨
